        <num>CHC 1032</num>
        <heading>1032.  Continuances</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1032.  Continuances
Upon a showing of good cause and notice to the opposing party, the court may grant, deny, or restrict a requested continuance of the proceeding.  The court shall avoid delays in resolving the status of the parent and in achieving permanency for the child.</p>
        </content>
